  "curatorsInsight": "\"Camang and Friends\" is a self-published children's book drawn from personal regret. While preparing for university, I became obsessed with admission to a prestigious institution and convinced myself that friendship was a distraction. I ignored calls, left messages unread, and shut out everyone close to me — only to find myself trapped in a loneliness far more painful than any academic pressure. This book translates that experience into a gentle metaphor: a small creature who leaves his companions behind, believing he must walk alone, only to learn that the journey without them is no journey at all. It is a quiet story about a truth I learned too late — that friendship is not a luxury, but a shelter from the most desperate kind of loneliness.\n\n\n\n\n",
  "historicalNarrative": "The \"Camang and Friends\" children's book is a significant project in Eungshin Kim's portfolio, showcasing the full pipeline from character design through story illustration to publication-ready layout using Photoshop and InDesign.",
